<h2 class="date">Mar 19, 2015</h2>
<div class="blogbody">
<h3 class="title">Project Progress Report</h3> 
<p> <b>Due by 11:59pm, 03/31/2015</b>. Each team should submit a brief
  (I expect you'll need ~2 pages, longer is fine too) progress report
  for your term project. You should cover:
<ul>
<li> A precise problem statement. You may also give some
  background/context/motivation for your problem.
<li> Some initial data analysis
<li> A description of your planned methods/approaches. This doesn't
  have to be in a lot of detail yet, but it's better if you start
  thinking about it earlier. 
<li> A list of resources you plan to use. Note: you should contact me
  as soon as possible if there are some data/software resources that
  you think you definitely need but don't have access for. 
<li> A schedule/list of milestones. If you are in a team of three, it
  is especially important for you to figure out a division of labor.
<li> An annotated bibliography of related work (That is, give the
not only the citation but also a couple of sentences saying why it's
  related/useful for your project.)
</ul>

